%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BArrest%20Void%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Orders%20Immediate%20Release%20Of%20NewsClick%20Founder%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ordered%20the%20release%20of%20NewsClick%20founder%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%2C%20declaring%20that%20his%20arrest%20by%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20was%20illegal.%20A%20bench%20of%20Justices%20BR%20Gavai%20and%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20today%20said%20the%20remand%20copy%20was%20not%20provided%20in%20the%20case%2C%20which%20makes%20his%20arrest%20void.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20hesitation%20in%20the%20mind%20of%20the%20court%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20were%20not%20provided%2C%20which%20vitiates%20the%20arrest.%20The%20appellant%20is%20entitled%20to%20release%20from%20custody%20after%20the%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20case.%20The%20remand%20order%20is%20invalid%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Justice%20Mehta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20held%20that%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20must%20be%20provided%20in%20writing%20to%20the%20accused%20in%20its%20March%20judgment%20in%20the%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20court%20will%20impose%20the%20bail%20conditions%20on%20Mr%20Purkayastha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Solicitor%20General%20(ASG)%20SV%20Raju%2C%20who%20argued%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20police%2C%20said%20while%20Mr%20Purkayastha's%20arrest%20has%20been%20declared%20void%2C%20it%20may%20not%20stop%20them%20from%20exercising%20their%20correct%20powers%20to%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20you%20are%20permitted%20to%20do%20under%20the%20law%2C%20you%20are%20permitted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20on%20April%2030%20questioned%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20hastily%20producing%20Mr%20Purkayastha%20before%20the%20magistrate%20without%20informing%20his%20lawyer%20after%20his%20arrest.%20The%20top%20court%20had%20also%20found%20it%20surprising%20that%20the%20remand%20order%20was%20passed%20even%20before%20his%20lawyer%20received%20his%20remand%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20lawyer%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20appearing%20for%20Mr%20Purkayastha%2C%20said%20he%20was%20arrested%20on%20October%203%20and%20produced%20before%20the%20magistrate%20at%206%20am%20the%20next%20day.%20Only%20legal%20aid%20lawyers%20and%20the%20additional%20public%20prosecutor%20were%20present%2C%20and%20Mr%20Purkayastha's%20lawyer%20was%20not%20informed%2C%20he%20said.%20When%20Mr%20Purkayastha%20objected%20to%20this%2C%20the%20investigating%20officer%20informed%20his%20lawyer%20through%20telephone%20and%20the%20remand%20application%20was%20sent%20to%20him%20on%20WhatsApp%2C%20said%20Mr%20Sibal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice%20require%20that%20Mr%20Purkayastha's%20lawyer%20be%20present%20when%20the%20remand%20order%20is%20passed%2C%20the%20bench%20had%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Purkayastha%20was%20arrested%20on%20October%203%20last%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%2C%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%20days%20after%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20investigation%20alleged%20that%20NewsClick%20had%20received%20funding%20from%20a%20network%20pushing%20Chinese%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%20chargesheet%20that%20ran%208%2C000%20pages%20including%20annexures%2C%20Delhi%20Police%20accused%20NewsClick%20and%20Mr%20Purkayastha%20of%20terror%20funding%20and%20promoting%20Chinese%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20also%20arrested%20NewsClick's%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakravarty%20on%20October%203%2C%20but%20in%20January%2C%20a%20court%20allowed%20him%20to%20turn%20approver%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715757600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fkd4gp7fg_newsclick-founder-prabir-purkayastha_625x300_10_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupre