e%20popular%20ChatGPT%20chatbot%2C%20which%20sparked%20a%20race%20among%20the%20world's%20largest%20tech%20companies%20for%20dominance%20in%20the%20emerging%20generative%20AI%20field%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fopenai-s-co-founder-ilya-sutskever-part-ways-with-chatgpt-maker-altman-124051500176_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fopenai-s-co-founder-ilya-sutskever-part-ways-with-chatgpt-maker-altman-124051500176_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fopenai-s-co-founder-ilya-sutskever-part-ways-with-chatgpt-maker-altman-124051500176_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Food%20Safety%20Body's%20New%20Carcinogen%20Check%20Method%20Amid%20Row%20Over%20Indian%20Spices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20sales%20ban%20on%20some%20Indian%20spices%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Singapore%20has%20prompted%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Authority%20of%20India%20(FSSAI)%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20new%20method%20to%20detect%20Ethylene%20Oxide%20in%20spices%2C%20top%20official%20sources%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chemical%20widely%20used%20in%20spices%20as%20a%20disinfectant%2C%20Ethylene%20Oxide%20is%20known%20to%20be%20carcinogenic.%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Singapore%20flagged%20its%20presence%20while%20imposing%20a%20ban%20on%20several%20products%20by%20Indian%20spice%20giants%20--%20MDH%20and%20Everest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20method%2C%20the%20sources%20said%2C%20is%20more%20accurate%20and%20has%20been%20validated%20by%20ICAR-National%20Research%20Centre%20For%20Grapes%20--%20the%20food%20safety%20regulator's%20national%20reference%20laboratory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20sources%2C%20this%20new%20method%20will%20be%20used%20to%20detect%20Ethylene%20Oxide%20in%20products%20imported%20to%20other%20countries%2C%20those%20exported%20from%20abroad%20and%20those%20manufactured%20for%20domestic%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20method%2C%20sources%20said%2C%20can%20detect%20Ethylene%20Oxide%20in%20packaged%20items%20too.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20action%20against%20Indian%20spices%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Singapore%2C%20over%201%2C500%20samples%20have%20been%20collected%20from%20markets%20and%20spice%20factories%20and%20sent%20for%20lab%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20Ethylene%20Oxide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20ban%20on%20Indian%20spices%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Singapore%20is%20a%20chemical%2C%20Ethylene%20Oxide%2C%20which%20is%20used%20as%20a%20disinfectant%20for%20spices.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20known%20to%20have%20carcinogenic%20properties.%20According%20to%20the%20International%20Agency%20For%20Research%20on%20Cancer%2C%20ethylene%20oxide%20is%20a%20Group%201%20carcinogenic%2C%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20enough%20evidence%20to%20conclude%20that%20it%20can%20cause%20cancer%20in%20humans%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20note%20announcing%20its%20decision%20to%20ban%20some%20Indian%20spices%2C%20Singapore%20said%20%26quot%3Bethylene%20oxide%20is%20allowed%20to%20be%20used%20in%20the%20sterilisation%20of%20spices%26quot%3B%2C%20but%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bexposure%20to%20this%20substance%20should%20be%20minimised%20as%20much%20as%20possible%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAlthough%20there%20is%20no%20immediate%20risk%20to%20consumption%20of%20food%20contaminated%20with%20low%20levels%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%2C%20long%20term%20exposure%20may%20lead%20to%20health%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20It%20added%20that%20ethylene%20oxide%20is%20not%20authorised%20for%20use%20in%20food%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20India%20Has%20Responded%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20has%20said%20India%20has%20one%20of%20the%20stringent%20norms%20for%20minimising%20pesticide%20residues%20in%20food%20items.%20%26quot%3BSome%20media%20reports%20are%20claiming%20that%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Authority%20of%20India%20(FSSAI)%20allows%2010%20times%20more%20pesticide%20residue%20in%20herbs%20and%20spices.%20Such%20reports%20are%20false%20and%20malicious%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Health%20Ministry%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20has%20one%20of%20the%20most%20stringent%20standards%20of%20Maximum%20Residue%20Limits%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20ban%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Singapore%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20has%20collected%20samples%20and%20sent%20them%20for%20testing.%20The%20Spices%20Board%20has%20come%20out%20with%20detailed%20guidelines%20for%20exporters%20to%20prevent%20ethylene%20oxide%20contamination%20in%20products%20shipped%20from%20India.%20The%20guidelines%20say%20exporters%20would%20avoid%20its%20use%20as%20a%20sterilising%20agent%20and%20ensure%20that%20transporters%2C%20warehouses%2C%20packaging%20material%20suppliers%20do%20not%20use%20this%20chemical%20at%20any%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMDH%20has%20denied%20the%20allegations%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%20use.%C2%A0%26quot%3BWe%20reassure%20our%20buyers%20and%20consumers%20that%20we%20do%20not%20use%20Ethylene%20Oxide%20at%20any%20stage%20of%20storing%2C%20processing%2C%20or%20packing%20our%20spices%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20amid%20reports%20of%20the%20ban%20last%20month.%20It%20had%20then%20said%20it%20had%20not%C2%A0received%20any%20communication%20from%20authorities%20in%20Singapore%20or%20Hong%20Kong.%20Everest%2C%20too%2C%20had%20denied%20that%20its%C2%A0products%20have%20been%20banned%20in%20Singapore%20and%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20said%20one%20of%20its%2060%20products%20sold%20in%20Singapore%20was%20being%20examined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715746500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F20