-president-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChuck%20Schumer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Schumer%20can't%20afford%20to%20lose%20the%20Senate%20seat%20if%20he%20wants%20to%20keep%20the%20party's%20slim%20majority%20in%20the%20chamber.%20Trone's%20point%20was%20that%20if%20the%20party%20has%20to%20spend%20money%20defending%20Maryland%2C%20it%20will%20have%20less%20available%20in%20other%20close%20races.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20spend%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20Trone%20told%20reporters%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%20%26quot%3BThat%20will%20give%20them%20a%20lot%20more%20flexibility%20to%20spend%20money%20elsewhere.%20And%20I'm%20sure%20that%20will%20appeal%20to%20the%20leader%20Schumer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Alsobrooks%20jumped%20into%20the%20Senate%20race%2C%20she%20touted%20her%20work%20as%20a%20domestic%20violence%20prosecutor%20and%20her%20experience%20leading%20the%20state's%20second-most%20populous%20jurisdiction%20in%20making%20the%20case%20for%20her%20candidacy.%20As%20county%20executive%2C%20she%20has%20been%20immersed%20in%20the%20nuts%20and%20bolts%20of%20local%20government%20and%20focused%20heavily%20on%20public%20safety%2C%20an%20issue%20that%20Republicans%20have%20sought%20to%20hammer%20Democrats%20on%20in%20recent%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Alsobrooks%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20endorsed%20by%20Maryland%20Democratic%20heavy%20hitters%20including%20Gov.%20Wes%20Moore%2C%20Sen.%20Chris%20Van%20Hollen%2C%20and%20veteran%20Rep.%20Steny%20Hoyer%20%E2%80%94%20had%20long%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20she%20felt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wusa9.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fmaryland%2Fdavid-trone-angela-alsobrooks-us-senate-larry-hogan-money-campaign-finance-data%2F65-6672201c-5d22-44bc-8791-71a28150b603%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrone's%20financial%20edge%20would%20not%20define%20the%20campaign%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%2