t%20the%20positions%20of%20critical%20weapons%20and%20sites%20that%20can%20then%20be%20targeted%20by%20guided%20tactical%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20heightened%20UAV%20presence%20is%20%26quot%3Ballowing%20their%20troops%20to%20accurately%20detect%20and%20destroy%20targets%20behind%20the%20front%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20senior%20research%20fellow%20Dr.%20Jack%20Watling%20of%20the%20London-based%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Fukraine-russia-beginning-compound-advantages%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20analysis%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20not%20had%20sufficient%20ISR%20for%20much%20of%20the%20war%20due%20to%20robust%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses%2C%20but%20as%20Ukraine%20reserves%20its%20limited%20interceptors%20for%20Russian%20jets%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BOrlan-10%20UAVs%20are%20now%20roaming%20far%20and%20wide%20over%20the%20front%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20better%20targeting%2C%20Russia%20is%20executing%20strikes%20behind%20the%20lines%20with%20Iskander%20tactical%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20rocket%20launchers%20like%20the%20Tornado-S%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attacks%20mirror%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20strikes%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20carried%20out%20Russia%20with%20rockets%20and%20missiles%20fired%20from%20US-provided%20High%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20Systems%2C%20or%20HIMARS.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224942%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20HIMARS%20rocket%20launching.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e63b9b4c17ff0019bb2e89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20M142%20HIMARS%20launches%20a%20rocket%20on%20the%20Bakhmut%20direction%20on%20May%2018%2C%202023%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Serhii%20Mykhalchuk%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20recent%20days%20Russia%20managed%20to%20strike%20a%20Ukrainian%20Buk%20air%20defence%20system%20and%20catch%20two%20Ukrainian%20helicopters%20on%20the%20ground%20while%20they%20refuelled%2C%26quot%3B%20Watling%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20other%20notable%20strikes%20of%20a%20kind%20that%20Russia%20has%20long%20aspired%20to%20but%20rarely%20successfully%20executed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Fmlrs-and-totality-battlefield%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunable%20to%20defeat%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20conduct%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20strikes%20as%20Ukraine's%20HIMARS%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20precision%2C%20targeting%20capabilities%2C%20and%20timely%20intel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20strikes%2C%20like%20the%20glide%20bomb%20attacks%20as%20Russian%20air%20forces%20have%20gained%20greater%20maneuverability%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efurther%20strain%20Ukraine's%20military%2C%20which%20is%20facing%20continuously%20depleting%20resources%20as%20Russian%20forces%20have%20510%2C000%20soldiers%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20and%20compounding%20advantages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20developments%20in%20Russian%20capabilities%20come%20as%20Russia%20sets%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20summer%20offensive%2C%20which%20could%20significantly%20pressure%20Kharkiv%20and%20areas%20around%20Zaporizhzhia%20before%20a%20push%20in%20the%20Donbas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20still%20waiting%20for%20more%20aid%20from%20its%20international%20partners%20that%20would%20boost%20increasingly%20weak%20areas%20in%20combat%20training%2C%20munitions%2C%20and%20industrial%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20long%20as%20Ukraine%20lacks%20materiel%2C%20Russia%20will%20begin%20to%20compound%20its%20advantages%2C%26quot%3B%20Watling%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20things%20that%20only%20Ukraine%20can%20do%2C%20though.%20Watling%20said%20Ukraine%20needs%20to%20mobilize%20a%20sufficient%20number%20of%20troops%20and%20establish%20a%20training%20pipeline%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20replace%20losses%20in%20its%20existing%20units%2C%20but%20also%20raise%20enough%20units%20to%20manage%20their%20rotation%20on%20and%20off%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20allows%20troops%20to%20be%20trained%20as%20well%20as%20the%20recovery%20of%20reserves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20if%20international%20partners%20fail%20to%20provide%20artillery%2C%20air%20defenses%2C%20electronic%20warfare%20systems%2C%20and%20other%20enablers%2C%20then%20Kyiv's%20forces%20will%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20outlook%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20bleak%2C%26quot%3B%20Watling%20wrote.%20But%20with%20the%20right%20effort%20and%20support%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20Russia's%20summer%20offensive%20can%20be%20blunted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-air-defense-problems-are-letting-russia-launch-new-strikes-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715720898000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6643cae2b4abc992e8c982ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-air-defense-problems-are-letting-russia-launch-new-strikes-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20more%20drones%20in%20the%20air%20as%20Ukraine%20rations%20its%20air%20defenses%2C%20Russia%20is%20conducting%20strikes%20it%20couldn't%20previously%20execute.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ella%20Sherman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-air-defense-problems-are-letting-russia-launch-new-strikes-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%